<p>Depiction of Mary and Jesus as a baby. The postcard is creased and slightly torn, and the frame is decaying. Titled <em>Vergine col Figlio </em>(Virgin and Son), it is a reproduction of a painting by the Spanish Baroque artist Murillo. It is a blank postcard made in Italy and framed in a plain wooden picture frame. Martins coveted all things foreign and mystical.</p>
<p>&ldquo;This image of the Madonna and child is typical of the sort of sentimental religious imagery popular in homes in the Karoo during Helen's life time. It may even have been in the home when Helen inherited the house from her parents&rdquo; (Graaff, personal communication 2017, 27 October).</p>